Whereas the work of service coordinators in the United States aids more than 1,000,000 low-income
			 Americans residing in publicly subsidized and other affordable housing
			 communities;

Whereas recent evidence shows that the provision of resident services through service coordinators
			 results in dramatic benefits for both residents and developers of
			 affordable housing;

Whereas residents in subsidized and affordable housing communities having a service coordinator
			 report higher satisfaction with their living environments and a heightened
			 desire to be productive members of their communities;

